    • get

      @NotNull public <T> @NotNull Optional<T> get(@NotNull @NotNull String... argRoute)
      Specify the route of Sub-Commands for reaching the argument desired.

      Example: 
       var argValue = result.<String>get("rootCommand", "subCommand", "argument")
      Returns the parsed value of the argument in the next command hierarchy:
      • rootCommand
        • subCommand
          • argument
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the value of the argument.
      Returns:
      An Optional containing the parsed value of the argument with the given name, or Optional.empty() if the argument was not found.
      Throws:
      CommandNotFoundException - If the command specified in the route does not exist
      ArgumentNotFoundException - If the argument specified in the route does not exist

    • getSubResult

      Returns the sub ParseResult with the given name. If none is found with the given name, CommandNotFoundException is thrown.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the sub command
      Returns:
      The sub ParseResult with the given name
      Throws:
      CommandNotFoundException - If no sub command with the given name is found
